{%- comment -%}
  antonio-cart-item.liquid
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Renders pizza-builder line item properties in the cart drawer.

  Usage:
    {% render 'antonio-cart-item', item: line_item %}

  Accepts:
    item  {Object}  — A Shopify cart line item object (cart.items[n] or
                      the `item` variable inside a for loop over cart.items).

  Behaviour:
    • Hidden properties (name starts with "_") are never displayed —
      standard Shopify convention.
    • The "Toppings" property has its upcharge appended when a sibling
      hidden property named "_topping_upcharge" exists on the same line item.
    • Each property row shows an emoji prefix determined by property name.
    • No output is rendered when the item has no visible properties.
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  comment
    Pre-flight: decide if there is anything to render at all.
    We also extract the topping upcharge value here so the Toppings
    row can use it without a second loop.
  endcomment

  assign has_visible_props  = false
  assign topping_upcharge   = nil

  for prop in item.properties
    assign prop_key        = prop.first
    assign prop_key_first  = prop_key | slice: 0
    assign prop_val        = prop.last

    if prop_key_first == '_'
      if prop_key == '_topping_upcharge' and prop_val != blank
        assign topping_upcharge = prop_val
      endif
    elsif prop_val != blank
      assign has_visible_props = true
    endif
  endfor
-%}

{%- if has_visible_props -%}
  <ul class="antonio-cart-item-props" aria-label="Pizza options">
    {%- for prop in item.properties -%}
      {%- liquid
        assign prop_key       = prop.first
        assign prop_val       = prop.last
        assign key_first_char = prop_key | slice: 0

        comment
          Skip hidden properties (name starts with "_")
        endcomment
        if key_first_char == '_'
          continue
        endif

        comment
          Skip blank values
        endcomment
        if prop_val == blank
          continue
        endif

        comment
          Determine emoji prefix from property name (case-insensitive comparison
          via downcase).
        endcomment
        assign prop_key_lower = prop_key | downcase

        if prop_key_lower == 'sauce'
          assign prop_emoji = '🍕'
        elsif prop_key_lower == 'cheese'
          assign prop_emoji = '🧀'
        elsif prop_key_lower == 'toppings'
          assign prop_emoji = '🍕'
        elsif prop_key_lower == 'cut'
          assign prop_emoji = '✂️'
        elsif prop_key_lower == 'notes' or prop_key_lower == 'note'
          assign prop_emoji = '📝'
        else
          assign prop_emoji = '•'
        endif
      -%}

      <li class="antonio-cart-item-props__row">
        <span class="antonio-cart-item-props__emoji" aria-hidden="true">{{ prop_emoji }}</span>
        <span class="antonio-cart-item-props__name">{{ prop_key }}:</span>
        <span class="antonio-cart-item-props__value">
          {%- comment -%}
            For the Toppings property, append the upcharge amount if present.
          {%- endcomment -%}
          {{- prop_val -}}
          {%- if prop_key_lower == 'toppings' and topping_upcharge != nil -%}
            <span class="antonio-cart-item-props__upcharge">&nbsp;(+{{ topping_upcharge | money }})</span>
          {%- endif -%}
        </span>
      </li>

    {%- endfor -%}
  </ul>
{%- endif -%}

{%- comment -%}
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  STYLES
  These are scoped to the snippet's class names and are safe
  to include here; Shopify deduplicates {% stylesheet %} blocks.
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
{%- endcomment -%}

<style>
  .antonio-cart-item-props {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 6px 0 0 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .antonio-cart-item-props__row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 4px;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #3D3D3D;
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding: 0;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .antonio-cart-item-props__emoji {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    font-size: 12px;
    line-height: 1;
    /* Align emoji baseline with text */
    position: relative;
    top: 1px;
  }

  .antonio-cart-item-props__name {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #3D3D3D;
    opacity: 0.75;
  }

  .antonio-cart-item-props__value {
    color: #3D3D3D;
    opacity: 0.85;
    word-break: break-word;
  }

  .antonio-cart-item-props__upcharge {
    color: #C8291E;   /* Marinara Red — marks the cost impact clearly */
    font-weight: 600;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  /* Mobile: tighten spacing slightly, no extra padding */
  @media screen and (max-width: 768px) {
    .antonio-cart-item-props {
      margin-top: 4px;
    }

    .antonio-cart-item-props__row {
      font-size: 12px;
      line-height: 1.55;
      padding: 0;
    }
  }
</style>

{%- comment -%}
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  INTEGRATION NOTES — how to include this snippet in Savor's
  cart-products.liquid
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  In snippets/cart-products.liquid, find the block that renders the
  product title and variant options for each line item. It is inside
  the <tbody role="rowgroup"> loop:

    {% for item in cart.items %}
      …
      <td class="cart-items__details …">
        <div class="cart-items__product-info">
          <p>
            <a href="{{ item.url }}" class="cart-items__title">
              {{- item.product.title -}}
            </a>
          </p>
          …
        </div>

        <div class="cart-items__variants-wrapper">
          …
          {%- if has_visible_properties -%}
            {{- ← the theme's built-in property <dl> block lives here -}}
          {%- endif -%}
          …
        </div>
      </td>
    {% endfor %}

  OPTION A — Replace the built-in property block entirely
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Replace the theme's `{%- if has_visible_properties -%} … {%- endif -%}`
  block (the one that renders the <dl class="cart-items__properties"> list)
  with:

    {% render 'antonio-cart-item', item: item %}

  OPTION B — Render alongside the built-in block (recommended for safety)
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Leave the theme's block in place and add the snippet immediately after
  the closing `{%- endif -%}` of the `has_visible_properties` check:

    {%- if has_visible_properties -%}
      {{- … theme's built-in <dl> … -}}
    {%- endif -%}

    {%- comment -%} Antonio pizza-builder properties — replaces plain list {%- endcomment -%}
    {% render 'antonio-cart-item', item: item %}

  NOTE: When using Option B the native <dl class="cart-items__properties">
  block will ALSO be shown for items that have properties. To avoid double-
  rendering, wrap the native block in a conditional that checks whether the
  item is a pizza-builder item, e.g.:

    {%- unless item.properties['_pizza_builder'] -%}
      {{- … native property block … -}}
    {%- endunless -%}
    {% render 'antonio-cart-item', item: item %}

  The `_pizza_builder` hidden property should be set to `"true"` (or any
  non-blank value) via AntonioCart.addItem(variantId, qty, { _pizza_builder: 'true', … })
  when submitting a pizza-builder form.

  ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
{%- endcomment -%}
